<r><c n="ID"><![CDATA[58]]></c><c n="a"><![CDATA[The expressions 'pure-blood', 'half-blood' and 'Muggle-born' have been coined by people to whom these distinctions matter, and express their originators' prejudices.  As far as somebody like Lucius Malfoy is concerned, for instance, a Muggle-born is as 'bad' as a Muggle.  Therefore Harry would be considered only 'half' wizard, because of his mother's grandparents.If you think this is far-fetched, look at some of the real charts the Nazis used to show what constituted 'Aryan' or 'Jewish' blood.  I saw one in the Holocaust Museum in Washington when I had already devised the 'pure-blood', 'half-blood' and 'Muggle-born' definitions, and was chilled to see that the Nazis used precisely the same warped logic as the Death Eaters.  A single Jewish grandparent 'polluted' the blood, according to their propaganda.]]></c></r>
